The paper deals with the problem of optimal distribution of AgI services over a wireless computing network, which involves both communication and computing resources. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also discusses flow scheduling and resource allocation algorithms, which are related to Information Theory (cs.IT) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. The paper also deals with queuing systems, which are related to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses applications such as personalized video streaming and augmented reality, which are related to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) and Graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. However, since the paper does not explicitly discuss computer vision or graphics, these sub-categories are less likely than the others mentioned.
